*What is a Collatz sequence*

Collatz sequence takes a number (call it `n`) and checks whether it is even or odd. If it is even, then the number is divided by 2 (`n&lt;-n/2`). If it is odd, then the number is divided by 3n+1 (`n&lt;-(3n+1)`). It ends when the number equals to 1 ( when n=1).

